  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>ultrasound</intervention_name>
    <description>A 3D volume of the uterus will be acquired by transabdominal sonography. The sweep angle was set at 85º and the probe will be kept perpendicular to the placental plate. The placenta will be examined and the size of the volume box will be adapted in such a way that the placenta fitted into it completely. The volume will then stored for later offline analysis.</description>
  </intervention>
